00:00:56.760 --> 00:00:58.440
What is thorium?

00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.880
Thorium is a slightly radioactive metal, which can be used for nuclear fuel, and which

00:01:02.880 --> 00:01:06.280
is roughly three times as abundant as uranium.

00:01:06.280 --> 00:01:13.400
Really all naturally occurring thorium is a single isotope, TH-232.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:21.600
Other isotopes such as TH-228, TH-230, and TH-234 exist only in trace amounts, and so

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.320
can be ignored for our purposes.

00:01:24.320 --> 00:01:28.640
Thorium oxide has long been used in applications such as gas, metals, and high-temperature

00:01:28.640 --> 00:01:35.000
ceramics, but has seen little use in nuclear power beyond some experimental reactors.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:40.920
While thorium differs from uranium, while thorium can be used in nuclear fuel, thorium 232

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:43.840
is fertile rather than fizzile.

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:48.040
That means that pure thorium is not itself directly capable of sustaining a nuclear

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:49.040
reaction.

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:54.760
Instead, it must be turned into a fizzile isotope by bombarding it with neutrons.

00:01:54.760 --> 00:02:00.440
In this respect, it is similar to uranium 238, which is the main isotope of uranium, which

00:02:00.440 --> 00:02:04.320
can be turned into fizzile and non-fizzile plutonium.

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:10.200
In the case of thorium 232, it can be turned into uranium 233, which is a fizzile isotope

00:02:10.200 --> 00:02:12.680
much like uranium 235.

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:18.840
However, unlike uranium 235, uranium 233 is not considered to be useful from making

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:21.240
nuclear weapons.

00:02:21.240 --> 00:02:26.520
Sources of thorium Currently, the largest non-reserves of thorium are in India, followed

00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:28.520
by Brazil and Australia.

00:02:28.520 --> 00:02:32.640
However, since there is currently a very limited market for thorium, there has not been

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:38.520
a lot of exploration done, and it is possible that very large reserves exist elsewhere.

00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:42.600
As a result of this, take attempts to list thorium reserves by country with a very large

