citing the difficult chemistry problems that thorium presents, and the effects this has on the

00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:25.080
types of molten salt used as compared to uranium. Lightwater reactors. Lightwater reactors,

00:10:25.080 --> 00:10:30.600
both the common pressurized water and boiling water reactor types, could use thorium fuel,

00:10:30.600 --> 00:10:35.640
but are not well suited to it. They would not achieve very good breeding ratios in terms of

00:10:35.640 --> 00:10:42.360
converting thorium 232 to uranium 233. A major drawback of these reactors is their lower

00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:48.440
neutron economy due to the use of a less effective moderator. However, there is some attraction

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:52.840
in terms of using them to get rid of surplus plutonium if that is what is desired.

