thorium fuel reactors. The main challenge facing the use of thorium is that it does not

00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:44.440
offer a lot of practical advantages over uranium. Like fast neutron reactors, using thorium

00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:50.280
was seen as a solution to a perceived future shortage of uranium. However, that shortage didn't

00:11:50.280 --> 00:11:56.920
materialize instead large new reserves of uranium were found. The cost of uranium is only a small

00:11:56.920 --> 00:12:01.880
part of the total cost of electric power from nuclear power plant, so uranium prices could

00:12:01.880 --> 00:12:07.560
rise significantly without affecting overall cost much. With enough of a rise in prices,

