00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:02.760
The spent fuel in additional blanket material from the pressurized heavy water reactors

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:10.520
would be reprocessed to extract the leftover uranium 233. This recovered uranium 233 would then

00:15:10.520 --> 00:15:15.800
be fed back into the fuel cycle to make more fuel with top-ups from fast-breeder reactors added

00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:21.560
as required. This fuel cycle would allow India to use its thorium reserves with a relatively

00:15:21.560 --> 00:15:28.520
small amount of uranium input. Current status India are working on the fast-breeder reactors

00:15:28.520 --> 00:15:32.840
which would be used to provide the seed material for thorium fuel in their pressurized heavy water

00:15:32.840 --> 00:15:38.840
reactors. India continue to pursue using thorium but they need to build up the rest of the fuel

00:15:38.840 --> 00:15:42.840
cycle which enables it before they can switch to thorium on a large scale.

